The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, June 10, 2003 				 Scalded in air
																								Mumbai, June 9 (PTI): A passenger sustained mild burn injuries after a coffee pot fell on him on board a Chennai-Mumbai Indian Airlines flight yesterday.																								A doctor immediately attended on the passenger, Girish Ramji, a management executive with a city bank. On arrival, Ramji was admitted to a city nursing home last night, airport sources said. Ramji was discharged today. The handle of the coffee pot  snapped scalding his thighs but ice water treatment by a  doctor on board helped. The patient was discharged today,  the sources added. 
